qas.question: What happens in a chennel transupport system?

answers.text: several proteins form a contiguous channel traversing the inner and outer membranes of the bacteria

qas.question: What three protien subunites are in the chennel transupport system?

answers.text: the ABC protein, membrane fusion protein (MFP), and outer membrane protein (OMP)[specify]

qas.question: What does this secretion system transport?

answers.text: various molecules, from ions, drugs, to proteins of various sizes
